data.content:
Three breaking changes hit your code. Here's each one:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` ŌĆö now takes `Func`, not `Expression<Func>`

Your expression-tree construction **won't compile** anymore. The new overload accepts a regular lambda, so conditional setters become trivial:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

Delete all the `Expression.Lambda` / `Expression.Call` machinery.

---

### 2. Complex type column names ŌĆö now auto-uniquified & full-path nested

Two related changes:

- **Same-named properties** across sibling complex types (e.g. `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street`) now get a disambiguating suffix instead of silently sharing a column. A new migration will rename one column.
- **Nested complex types** now use the full path: `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` maps to column `Payment_BillingAddress_City` instead of the old `BillingAddress_City`.

**If you have an existing database**, pin the old names to avoid a migration-breaking rename:

```csharp
// Sibling complex types ŌĆö force shared column name if that was intentional,
// or accept the new unique names if the old behavior was a bug.
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress,
        p => p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress,
        p => p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
});

// Nested complex types ŌĆö pin old column name
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>()
    .ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment)
    .ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress)
    .Property(a => a.City)
    .HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
```

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` ŌĆö new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method on this interface now requires an additional `string logCommandText` parameter (used for redacted SQL logging):

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)   // ŌåÉ new parameter
    {
        // Use logCommandText for logging (constants may be redacted)
        // Use command.CommandText for the actual executed SQL
    }
}
```

Add the parameter to **every** method on the interface (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.).
